1
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Silav û rêz bînerên me yên ezîz. Lê her gundekî çîrokek, û
li her malekê çîrokek.
 
Greetings and respects, our dear viewers. In every village
there is a story, and in every house there is a story.

2
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Îro em ê derbasî çar malbatan bibin, çar çîrokan bi hev re
nas bikin.
 
Today we will visit four families, we will get to know four
stories together.

3
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Wekî tê zanîn, me berê xwe da gundê Berdêna, navçeya
Tirbespiyê.
 
As is known, we headed to the village of Bardena, in the
Tirbespiye district.

4
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Em ê derbasî cem çar malbetan bibin, çar çîrokan em ê bi hev
ra bizanibin.
 
We will visit four families, we will get to know four
stories together.

5
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Çîrokên xemgîn, çîrokên dilêcan in.
 
Sad stories, heart-wrenching stories.

6
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Bînerên me yên ezîz, malbeta siftê em ê derbas bin. Hat
naskirin malbeta, mala Yehya Eşo.
 
Our dear viewers, we will visit the first family. It is
known as the family of Yahya Esho.

7
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Çîrokek gelekî xemgîn e. Tûşî zehmetiyê ra derbas dibe.
 
It is a very sad story. They are going through difficulties.

8
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Lê naha bi hev ra em ê derbasî vê malê bibin, em ê çîroka
wan ji nêzîk va nas bikin.
 
But now together we will enter this house, we will get to
know their story closely.

9
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Destê sipî bi xêrê dirêj dibe. Apê Elî Daxwaz li bajarê
Amerîka, me derbasî çar malbetan kir, ji bo çar malbetan jî
em dilê wan şa bikin.
 
The white hand is extended with goodness. Uncle Ali Dakhwaz
in the city of America, had us visit four families, to make
the hearts of four families happy.

10
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:39,000
Bînerên me yên ezîz, naha jî em ê derbasî vê malbetê bin.
 
Our dear viewers, now we will visit this family too.

11
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:45,000
Rewşa wan jî gelekî zehmet e, eger em malbata heşt neh salan
bi paş da bibin.
 
Their situation is also very difficult, if we take the
family eight or nine years back.

12
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Piştî wê em dibînin derbasbûn gundê xwe dibin.
 
After that we see them returning to their village.

13
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Lê di gundê xwe jî malxaniyê wan nîne, wan ketiye xaniyekî,
û ev xanî jî ne yê xwe ye.
 
But they don't even have a house in their village, they have
entered a house, and this house is not theirs.

14
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:57,000
Em spasiya wan dikin ji ber cîhdana vê malbatê.
 
We thank them for providing shelter to this family.

15
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Ev malbat rûniştîbû, qumbeledek di nav wan da ket, zarokek
da peqîn. Çend kes... Çend zarok, keçikên wan, giran ketin.
 
This family was sitting, a bomb fell among them, and
exploded on a child. Several people... Several children,
their daughters, were seriously injured.

16
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:09,000
Jê yek, keçikek heye çavên xwe nabîne.
 
One of them, there is a girl who cannot see with her eyes.

17
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Berî vê em hatin derbasî cem bûn, eva cara duyem e em tên.
 
Before this we visited them, this is the second time we are
coming.

18
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:29,000
Lê îro jî me xwest em derbasî cem Cano bin, em ê bi hev ra
çîroka Cano ji nêzîk va nas bikin.
 
But today also we wanted to visit Cano, together we will get
to know Cano's story closely.

19
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Rojbaş ana, te fêhm kir Cano? ... Cano.
 
Good morning mother, did you understand Cano? ... Cano.

20
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:47,000
Cano ... Cano
 
Cano ... Cano

21
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Dê ka xêra xwe îne em kêvê ra paqij kin.
 
Bring it please, let's clean this here.

22
00:02:49,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Ka xêra xwe îne kê paqij ke.
 
Bring it please, who should clean it.

23
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:27,000
Çapik Cano, ra Çapik.
 
Fast Cano, get up fast.

24
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Lê pûzê lê neye, çapik.
 
Don't hit her nose, fast.

25
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Cano, Cano
 
Cano, Cano

26
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Berî her tiştî ez spasiya we dikim, we deriyê xwe ji me ra
vekir. Em her gav em derbasî ba we dibin em bi keyf in we
dibînin.
 
First of all, I thank you, you opened your door for us.
Every time we visit you, we are happy to see you.

27
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:45,000
Ehlen we sehlen. Dîtina we, ji me re rojeke xweş e, we xêr
anî.
 
Welcome. Seeing you is a beautiful day for us, you brought
goodness.

28
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,000
Ji berî çi te rewa dîtin?
 
Since when have you seen this situation?

29
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,000
Elhemdulillah ji barê çi re.
 
Praise be to God for everything.

30
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Yanî me mualecat jî kirin, û nizam yanî.
 
I mean we also did treatments, and systematically.

31
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Vê, sal nîvek, di sal e, nayê bîra min, ji xatirê şixlek din
re.
 
Yes, for a year and a half, two years, I can't remember,
because of other work.

32
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,000
Heşt neh salan e?
 
Is it eight or nine years?

33
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:00,000
Deh sal in, ehe de bêm.
 
It is ten years, that's what I'll say.

34
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:03,000
Dixwazim hinekî di çîroka gêndîş de ez xeberdekî dixwazim...
tiştên dest pê bikî.
 
I want you to talk a little bit about this incident... start
with it.

35
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:06,000
Ez ê kî bînim, de kî de dest pê bikim?
 
What should I bring up, where should I start?

36
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,000
Bina we?
 
See here?

37
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:10,000
Yek bihî, şeş mehekî rind bû.
 
It was one, she was fine for six months.

38
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:10,000
Şeş mehekî şûn da seqetiyê lê ketîye. Vê ew birî dixtor de.
Dixtor gote çûkek de dema te ewê amade bikî.
 
Yes.

39
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:18,000
Şeş mehekî şûn da seqetiyê lê ketîye. Vê ew birî dixtor de.
Dixtor gote çûkek de dema te ewê amade bikî.
 
After six months a disability affected her. Then she was
taken to a doctor. The doctor said you should prepare this
child.

40
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:23,000
Hatin malbavê, heftekî di de çûn. Da dî zeîf bî û istel wan
xist.
 
They came to her father's family, they went after a week.
Then she got weak again and they struck them.

41
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Heşt neh salan bi paş da bibin, naha hê jî we rûyê xwe da
gundê Berdîna?
 
Let's go back eight or nine years, now you still directed
yourselves to Berdîna village?

42
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Kes dikê di xaniyê ke... ti kar dikin der barê canê xwe tu
çawa dikî?
 
Anyone who stays in someone's house... how do you do
anything for your soul's sake?

43
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Çawa derbas dikî heyata xwe?
 
How do you spend your life?

44
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:41,000
Yanî heyata me... e... bi xwe yanî ez nizanim wille ez fehm
nakim. De şixil hebe dê şixil kim, de tunebê hew dî... dî
nahake de em.
 
I mean our life... well... by myself I mean I swear I don't
know, I don't understand. If there is work I'll work, if
there isn't then that's it... right now we...

45
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,000
Dê tu dikî kar?
 
So do you work?

46
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,000
Hebe dikî... şixil tunebe ji...
 
If there is I do... if there is no work...

47
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:48,000
Mînak dî carek çûyîna ez hatim di cem de da ku keçek du
keçên wusa ti dixebitî.
 
For example, the other time I came to you, you were working
with one or two girls like that.

48
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:55,000
Wisa çûyê wexta ti çûyê da... dixtor telefûn kir, ew birin
emelyatê. Wê emelyatê derxistin... Di de çûn a.
 
It was like that, when you went... the doctor called, they
took her to surgery. They brought her out of the surgery...
Then they left.

49
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Xirab dibî tiştek di wê di zeîf dibî.
 
She gets worse, she gets weak in something.

50
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Ne weza... ew a em rûniştî bûn...
 
The situation... we were sitting...

51
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Em rûniştî bûn li malan, em rûniştî bûn qûnbeleyek nava me
da, peqî...
 
Yes.

52
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Em rûniştî bûn li malan, em rûniştî bûn qûnbeleyek nava me
da, peqî...
 
We were sitting in the house, we were sitting, a bomb went
off among us, it exploded...

53
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Ew qiçkên min ji giran ketin, keçek piçek serê qîza min di
sere wê de çûn, qîzkê xwe ji çav çû, qîzika din ji çav çû.
 
My kids were heavily injured, a piece of my girl's head went
into her head, one girl lost her eyes, the other girl lost
her eyes.

54
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:14,000
Û kilpatî me ye zêdetir sere wê hişabû.
 
And it affected us too, mostly her head was hurt.

55
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:22,000
Û lawkê min e din e Mehemed, ewa hane dirêje, ev çûyek da
çû, û ew çavê wî jî xazî pê ketiye xazî. Ne xazî ye hewşê
gazî ye.
 
And my other boy Mohammed, he is tall like that, he went on
a trip, and his eyes were affected by gas. If not gas, it's
like gas.

56
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:27,000
Û elhemdulillah, şikir... bi her halî, am di... em heta
naha, dîsa elhemdulillah em wiha na derbas dikin îşte.
 
And praise be to God, thanks... in any case, we... until
now, again praise be to God we are spending it like this.

57
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:32,000
Me xwest ku em vê rojê derbasî cem we bibin. Em Cano dilê wê
şa bikin îro.
 
We wanted to visit you today. To make Cano's heart happy
today.

58
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,000
Elhemdulillah.
 
Praise be to God.

59
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:37,000
Em di her demekê em dî dê bişopînin ew... Cano alî we bi xwe
ye...
 
We will follow up every time... Cano is with you yourself...

60
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,000
Xwedê siheta we xweş bike.
 
May God give you good health.

61
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,000
Weke di te de ke.
 
And to you too.

62
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,000
Tê Cano.
 
You're coming Cano.

63
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,000
Dema tê tu naz dikî?
 
When you come, do you recognize?

64
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:44,000
Hê?
 
Huh?

65
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Xaniyê we ye?
 
Is it your house?

66
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Na wille nî me ye. Ye xelkê ye, man ti tune ye.
 
No, by God, it's not ours. It belongs to the people, I don't
have anything.

67
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,000
Hawşek te, xaniyek te nîne?
 
You don't have a yard, a house?

68
00:05:55,000 --> 00:06:13,000
Na hawş û me tune ne.
 
No, we don't have a yard.

69
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:17,000
Ez wek... vê emanetê teslîmî te dikim, li ser navê apê Elî.
 
As I... hand this trust over to you, on behalf of Uncle Ali.

70
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,000
Ji bajarê Amerîka...
 
From the city of America...

71
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:22,000
Wî xwest çîrokek din li gundê we... em bibînin.
 
He wanted us to see another story in your village.

72
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:25,000
Û me dît yekem tişt em werin ba we... me xwest em vê emanetê
teslîmî we bikin.
 
And we saw the first thing is to come to you... we wanted to
hand over this trust to you.

73
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Spas ji apê Elî ra, Xwedê xêra wî binivîse, Xwedê emrê wî
dirêj bike.
 
Thanks to Uncle Ali, may God write his good deed, may God
lengthen his life.

74
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,000
Xwedê ji wî razî be Xwedê siheta wî xurt bike, Xwedê emrê wî
dirêj bike.
 
May God be pleased with him, may God strengthen his health,
may God lengthen his life.

75
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Em gelkî kêfxweş bûn, Xwedê wî jî kêfxweş bike. Înşelah
zarokê wî hêjayî wî bin.
 
We were very happy, may God make him happy too. Hopefully
his children will be worthy of him.

76
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:40,000
Ez hêvîdar im... ev emaneta wî ye... belkî me hinekî dilê
Cano xweş kiribe, gava yek dilê wê xweş bike ewqasî kêfxweş
dibe.
 
I am hopeful... this is his trust... maybe we made Cano's
heart happy a little, when someone makes her heart happy she
becomes so happy.

77
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Rojbûna Cano ya çend salî bû te xwest pîroz bikî?
 
Cano's birthday, how old was she that you wanted to
celebrate?

78
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:48,000
Welle her sê sal... nexweş ket... welle neket bîra min min
pîroz bike.
 
By God, every three years... she got sick... by God, I
didn't remember to celebrate it.

79
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Ez hêvîdar im ku ji nexweşiyê xelas bibe û em rojbûna wê
pîroz bikin.
 
I hope that she gets rid of the illness and we celebrate her
birthday.

80
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Û her weha em spasiya te dikin, ev malbata ku hûn mecbûr man
hûn werin vir.
 
And also we thank you, this family that you were forced to
come here.

81
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Welle xêra mala Xwedê ye... em spasiya wan dikin...
 
By God, it's the charity of the house of God... we thank
them...

82
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:01,000
Bê guman Xwedê jê razî be...
 
Undoubtedly, may God be pleased with them...

83
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:05,000
Lê em hêvîdar in Xwedê xêra wan binivîse, em bi we re di nav
alîkariyê da bin.
 
But we hope God writes their good deeds, we will be in
assistance with you.

84
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,000
Gelek spas ji bo we, Xwedê we parêze.
 
Thank you very much, may God protect you.

85
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Çawa be em ê her dem bi we re bin.
 
However it may be, we will always be with you.

86
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:16,000
Welle mal ava be. Xêr û xweşî be. Xwedê dilê we şa bike.
Xwedê xêra wî qebûl bike.
 
By God, may your house prosper. May there be goodness and
well-being. May God make your hearts happy. May God accept
his charity.

87
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:19,000
Cano tu jî spasiya wî bike, xêra te...
 
Cano, you also thank him, please...

88
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:22,000
De Cano xatirê te.
 
So Cano, goodbye.

89
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,000
De xatirê we, oxir be.
 
So goodbye, have a good journey.

90
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:44,000
Xatirê we.
 
Goodbye.

91
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:18,000
Bînerên me yên ezîz, em ê naha jî derbasî malbateke din
bibin, malbeta xalê Ebdî.
 
Our dear viewers, now we will pass to another family, Uncle
Abdi's family.

92
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:23,000
Du keçên xwe û xortekî xwe. Cîwan in... xortekî wan cîwan e,
berî bi çar salan ew li xaniyekî da ket.
 
His two daughters and a son. They are young... one of their
sons is young, four years ago he fell in a house.

93
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:26,000
Çîrokek gelekî giran, gelekî xemgîn e.
 
A very heavy story, very sad.

94
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:45,000
De naha bi me ra werin, em bi hev ra kerem kin, çîrokê ji
nêzîk va nas bikin.
 
So now come with us, please let's go together, to get to
know the story from close up.

95
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:50,000
Bînerên me yên ezîz, berî em çîroka van bi hev ra nas
bikin...
 
Our dear viewers, before we get to know their story
together...

96
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,000
Em di derbasî cem evîn bin.
 
We will pass to this family.

97
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,000
Em ê ji dêla wan re spasiya wan bikin.
 
We will thank them on their behalf.

98
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:58,000
Me dixwast... apê me Elî, li bajarê Amerîka dixwast, dilê
her kesekî şa bike.
 
We wanted... our Uncle Ali, in the city of America wanted to
make everyone's heart happy.

99
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Destê sipî bi xêrê dirêj dikin...
 
They extend a white hand with goodness...

100
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:05,000
Sibê bixêr e. De rabe de.
 
Good morning. Get up.

101
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Destê xwe ke. De ka çap ka ewan re.
 
Give your hands. Give them a high five.

102
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:12,000
De pifê ke, ey sate destê we bigrim.
 
Give a kiss, well done let me hold your hands.

103
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:14,000
Helal e.
 
Well done.

104
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,000
Tu çawa yî?
 
How are you?

105
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:35,000
Te çawa ye?
 
How are you?

106
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:40,000
Xalê Ebdîn berî her tiştî em spasiya te dikin em îro mêvanên
we ne.
 
Uncle Abdin, first of all, we thank you, we are your guests
today.

107
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:43,000
Te deriyê xwe ji me re vekiriye, em pir kêfxweş in.
 
You have opened your door to us, we are very happy.

108
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:49,000
Ehlen we sehlen, ser serê min û ser çavê min hûn hatin û
bixêr hatina we ser serê min û ser çavê min e, qenata we ya
Telat Efrînî.
 
Welcome, you came on my head and on my eyes and your welcome
is on my head and on my eyes, your channel Telat Efrini.

109
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:58,000
Û inşallah Xwedê zêde bike û Xwedê... roştir be û zêdetir be
û pêşdatir be û serketî xwaştir be. Xwedê canê we sax be.
 
And hopefully may God increase it and may God... make it
brighter and more and more advanced and more successful. May
God give you health.

110
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:05,000
Gelek spas ya te, Xalê Ebdîn. Ez dixwazim hinekî tu li ser
nexweşiya Evon ji nêzîk ve nas bikim.
 
Thank you very much, Uncle Abdin. I want you to talk a
little bit so I can get to know Evan's illness closely.

111
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:10,000
Welleh berî wî we ku teqriben jokê xetî, çar sal e, çar sal
û nîv ha nakê ye.
 
By God, before him, it was approximately, he was a child,
it's been four years, four and a half years like this.

112
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:21,000
Me bir Tirkiyê, me li xestexana erebî me bir Tirkiyê
emeliyat kir ne necehî, paşî piştê du sala meş ûna me teglê
emeliyatek dî kir.
 
We took him to Turkey, we were in the Arab hospital, we took
him to Turkey, we operated on him, it wasn't successful,
then after two years we walked and did another operation.

113
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:25,000
Nexweşiyek wisa ye ku wekî evçenda meş tina ye.
 
It's an illness like he cannot walk at all.

114
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:31,000
Û em lê heyirî ne, yanî qenciya nexweşiyê ji me re xuya
nabe. Em tebê lê dinêrin.
 
And we are amazed at it, I mean the goodness of the disease
is not visible to us. We are trying our best.

115
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,000
Loma wa cî rûniştî na rabê?
 
So he cannot stand up from his sitting position?

116
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:37,000
Û rûniştî ye û qesd era tedawiye hefte hefte da kiriye û
heta dika girî.
 
And he is sitting and he has been treated intentionally for
weeks and he even cries.

117
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,000
Temenê wî çend e?
 
How old is he?

118
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:47,000
Temenê wî şeş e û naha ev derman vira kire mane me ev kire
ha wexta şêst dolar ye di teneke derman em dikirin şêst
dolar e. Her yekî sî dolar e.
 
