246
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:54,000
Xwedê temenê te dirêj bike.
 
May God prolong your life.

247
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:57,000
Xwedê ji te razî be.
 
May God be pleased with you.

248
00:23:57,000 --> 00:24:00,000
Tu çend sal in elbedê bi vî avayî yî? Neha em hildin
 
How many years have you been like this? Now let's see

249
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:02,000
heşt sal ez... Xwedê te dîtibû.
 
eight years I... God saw you.

250
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:05,000
Heta we da Xwedê te xweş e?
 
Until God makes you well?

251
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:06,000
Heşt sal e.
 
It's been eight years.

252
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:09,000
Heşt sal tu nediketiya we ne?
 
You didn't fall down for eight years, did you?

253
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:10,000
Nediketiya.
 
No, I didn't fall.

254
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:11,000
Belê gundê we ye.
 
Yes, it's your village.

255
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:29,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

256
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:31,000
Tu dixwazî ez televîzyonê te... ez qenala te seyr dikim?
 
Do you want me to watch your television... your channel?

257
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:32,000
A belê.
 
Ah, yes.

258
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:33,000
Qenala da seyr dikî?
 
You watch the channel?

259
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,000
A...
 
Ah...

260
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:35,000
Tê xema xwe bîne.
 
Take care of yourself.

261
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:38,000
Em kê kê li cem xwe li ser qenatê..
 
We are together with everyone on the channel.

262
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:41,000
Ez qenala te me.
 
I am your channel.

263
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:44,000
Tu pir kesî evan tiştan re te dît.
 
You saw many people with these things.

264
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:47,000
Em derbasî cem we bûn evan ezîzan li ber dilê me.
 
We went to you dear ones close to our hearts.

265
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:49,000
Em derbasî cem hemiya bûn.
 
We went to everyone.

266
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:52,000
Her yek piştî wî em derbas bûn, pêk hatin sobeyê...
 
After each one we passed, we came to the stove.

267
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:53,000
Xwedê da wî.
 
God gave him.

268
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:55,000
Em pir kêfxweşin bi dîtina we.
 
We are very happy to see you.

269
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:58,000
Neha ez wekî kesekî bi navê bavê bazare Amerika dibêje.
 
Now I'll speak to someone whose father says he is in the
American market.

270
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:59,000
Navê xwe Alî Amerkî ye.
 
His name is Ali Amerki.

271
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:03,000
Eza bixwazim hinekê tu dua ji wî re bikî, ji ber ku ew
kincan xelas dike,
 
I want you to pray for him a little, because he's clearing
clothes,

272
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,000
çiqas ku ta bêkî tu...
 
as much as you can.

273
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:08,000
Xwedê seba xwe ji te re bike.
 
May God reward you.

274
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:10,000
Tu dixwazî tu wî re dua bikî.
 
You want to pray for him.

275
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:11,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

276
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:15,000
Tu xwedî tu ev tişta te xwe bikirî. Tu dikarî tu... tu şikir
ji vî re bikî.
 
You have your own things to buy. You can... you can thank
him.

277
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:23,000
Xwedê seba we wî bike. Şikir ji vî re bikim...
 
May God reward you. I thank him...

278
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:27,000
Tu bixwazî tiştên te ji kerema xwe bikî.
 
You can do whatever you want.

279
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:29,000
... te şikir tiştê Xwedê te kirî...
 
You thanked him for what God did to you...

280
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:32,000
Dê neha em baybay kin kemberê wî, de...
 
Let's wave goodbye to him now...

281
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:33,000
Bêrî...
 
See you...

282
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:53,000
Hemûd dibêje qet, ...
 
Hamoud says no...

283
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:35,000
Bînerê me yê ezîz, eza sipasiya we bikim. Em gihiştin dawiya
xelekê xwe.
 
Our dear viewer, I thank you. We have reached the end of our
episode.

284
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:40,000
Piştî wê ez e sipasiyê kadroya xwe û teswîrê bikim. Bavê
Kenî Hecî.
 
After that I thank our crew and the photographer. Father of
Keni Haci.

285
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:42,000
Û Mamoste Ehmed wî nîvisiya.
 
And Teacher Ahmed wrote it.

286
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:45,000
Teswîrê me herduya evî nivîsî bê.
 
Our photography of the two of us wrote this.

287
00:27:45,000 --> 00:27:48,000
Piştî we em spasî yê vê malbatê ya ku derbazî cem bûn a.
 
After you, we thank this family who came to visit us.

288
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:49,000
Xwedê temenê wî dirêj bike.
 
May God prolong his life.

289
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:51,000
Çîrokên me jî bi her û pir xweş bûn.
 
Our stories were very nice.

290
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:57,000
Li benda me bin. Xelkê dê vira re heke xweştir be, û ji vega
jî dartir be.
 
Wait for us. If people here will be nicer, and from now on
more generous.

291
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:59,000
Gava me yek ji me ya xwezayî mişke.
 
When one of us naturally disappears.

292
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:01,000
Piştî wê em ê spasikî mezin
 
After that, we'll give a big thank you

293
00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:05,000
ji apê Alî re bikim ku bazara Emerka vî alîkariyê me,
 
to Uncle Ali from the American market, who helped us,

294
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:07,000
ku ev xeleka jî di nav wî hat çêkirin.
 
that this episode was made with his help.

295
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:09,000
Dê her gundekî di rûyê kekê...
 
For every village on the face of the earth...

296
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:11,000
û her malekê çîrokek, çîroka me jî...
 
and a story for every home, our story too...

297
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:13,000
her yekî... galekî xweş bûyin,
 
each one... had a very nice story,

298
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:14,000
û bi we re, em pir kêfxweş bûn.
 
and with you, we were very happy.

299
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:19,000
Ez bi wê re bim, xatirê te.
 
I'll leave you with that, goodbye.

